<|startoftext|>Dish: walnut bread pudding   mccormick
Directions: put the milk , butter , and walnuts into the bowl of the food processor and whizz to a mixture of the ingredients
add the walnuts last and process to a powdery texture
add salt and 1 / 2 teaspoon sugar and process to a smooth texture
set aside a little bowl to use for this step so the mixture can be stored in a dry place
meanwhile , place the egg yolks into the bowl of the food processor and whizz about a minute to a paste of the consistency of ground sesame seeds
add the walnuts last and process just to a thick texture
add the baking powder to the mixture and whiz with the motor just until the butter melts and the paste comes to a smooth consistency , about 2 minutes
transfer the mixture to the hot bowl of a food processor and whiz the desired consistency with the motor until the consistency of powdery crumbs , about 2 minutes or so
transfer to a serving bowl or small plate and stir in the warm milk
chill until it has been thoroughly chilled', if the pudding is just chilled , i've used a baking dish so i still make sure there is enough sauce at the bottom for the pudding to spread evenly, 'the pudding will thaw out in an instant-read thermometer at this point , but this is better a few hours later
i served it with vanilla yogurt topping with almond whipped cream
the pudding is also good served with a sprinkle of chives & powdered sugar'<|endoftext|>
